text.p: These are some of the leading stories in the official Iraqi press on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.
- A French cultural delegation to start visit to Iraq on Thursday.
- Turkish Foreign Minister calls for implementing Iraq's oil-for-food deal signed with the U.N.
- Arab and world firms express readiness to supply Iraq with food and medicine in accordance with the deal.
(The above stories were also carried by IRAQ and QADISSIYA)
- Bulgarian businessmen specialising in medicine production arrive in Baghdad.
- Iraq to hold a conference for Iraqi expatriates.
